name: 2-Methoxyethanol
Reason: 2-Methoxyethanol is a derivative of ethanol, which has a melting point of -114.1°C. The presence of a methoxy group (-OCH3) increases the melting point due to the potential for hydrogen bonding and dipole-dipole interactions. The methoxy group can be estimated to increase the melting point by approximately +10°C.
